creator: Charlotte Mary Yonge
description:
LibriVox recording of Young Folks' History of Germany by Charlotte Mary Yonge.
Read in English by Kara Shallenberg; KHand
An entertaining history for "young folks", covering the history of Germany from the ancient tribes of pre-Roman times to Wilhelm I (1870-1877). - Summary by Kara
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
